{
  "text": "To overcome metamorphic viruses' obfuscation techniques, semantic based features become into new anti-virus researches in recent years. The most crucial concern related to semantic methods is that it requires a large amount of prerequisites works. It normally takes a great deal of time to form a proper semantic signature. In addition, the semantic methods cannot be used onthe-fly [CITATION_1] . It is also considerable to notice that a method, which spends an unreasonable time to analyze and detect a mutated variation of a virus, is not practicable, even it be able to detect with high degree of accuracy.",
  "citation_candidates": [
